WEBVTT



00:00:08.736 --> 00:00:15.072
Hello, and thank you for joining us as we continue to walk with Jesus through Lent as he heads to the cross.

00:00:15.072 --> 00:00:19.776
This week we found ourselves in Matthew 17 in the region of Galilee.

00:00:19.808 --> 00:00:26.528
As we look at the passage, we find Jesus, Peter, James and John rejoining the crowd,

00:00:26.432 --> 00:00:31.488
And they find that the other disciples are experiencing a spiritual obstacle.

00:00:31.840 --> 00:00:39.712
A man with a son who's demonically impressed has come to the disciples for healing, and they've been unable to drive the demon out thus far.

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:43.488
And so the man comes to Jesus and asks for him to intervene.

00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:51.520
Now, Jesus' response might startle us at first. He says, You unbelieving and perverse generation, how long shall I put up with you?

00:00:51.936 --> 00:00:54.976
But then Jesus immediately heals the boy.

00:00:54.752 --> 00:00:58.944
And so we know that these words don't reveal a heart unwilling to act.

00:00:58.688 --> 00:01:04.416
but rather that Jesus is trying to remind us of the crucial element in any spiritual journey.

00:01:04.416 --> 00:01:05.920
And that's faith.

00:01:06.272 --> 00:01:16.320
Now, as Jesus is saying these words, he's actually echoing what God said to the Israelite nation in Numbers 14 when they refused to go in and take the land.

00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:22.816
land because 10 of the 12 spies had come back and said, we can't do this. There are giants in the land. Right.

00:01:22.688 --> 00:01:32.736
And so God says, how long shall I put up with you despite my clear presence with you, despite all the miracles you've seen? You still don't have faith that you can overcome these obstacles as long as

00:01:32.256 --> 00:01:34.240
As long as I am with you.

00:01:34.304 --> 00:01:44.352
And so as Jesus echoes these words, he's essentially saying to the disciples, "I've been with you. You've seen my miracles. Why is it that you lack the faith that while I'm

00:01:43.872 --> 00:01:47.776
While I'm with you and in my name, you can overcome the obstacle. Thank you.

00:01:47.552 --> 00:01:49.472
Of this demonic oppression.

00:01:49.984 --> 00:02:00.032
And so Jesus tells the disciples, "If only you had faith the size of a mustard seed, you could stay into this mountain, be thrown into the sea, nothing will be impossible for you."

00:01:59.552 --> 00:02:00.480
For you

00:02:00.288 --> 00:02:02.720
As long as they remember Jesus is with them.

00:02:02.944 --> 00:02:12.992
now the placement of this passage is really great because peter james and john as they rejoined the crowd with jesus they had just descended down from the mount of transfiguration.

00:02:12.512 --> 00:02:13.664
Figuration.

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:22.560
They had literally seen the full glory of Jesus unveiled, and seen Emmanuel God with us in his full glory.

00:02:22.784 --> 00:02:30.208
And so the reminder for us in these passages is that Jesus was with them. God was with them.

00:02:30.272 --> 00:02:40.320
And we might think in our own spiritual journey, "Sure, if Jesus was with me, I'd have faith to overcome my obstacles. If there was a pillar of fire with me, I'd have faith to do whatever

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:42.368
Whatever God called me to you on my spiritual journey.

00:02:42.688 --> 00:02:46.560
But the encouragement is that we should remember that God is with us.

00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:54.016
That when we place our faith in Jesus, the Holy Spirit indwells us. We have Emmanuel, God with us.

00:02:54.048 --> 00:03:01.312
And so the key to bold faith in our spiritual journey is not a journey absent from obstacles,

00:03:01.056 --> 00:03:03.680
But remember that God is with us.

00:03:04.032 --> 00:03:14.080
I had a chaplain in college that every year would share the same message with incoming freshmen. He'd recount the story of the bad report about giants in the land and he'd tell the students in their bedroom.

00:03:13.600 --> 00:03:18.656
and their parents listen here at this college there are no Giants in the land

00:03:18.880 --> 00:03:22.784
And while he meant to encourage them, I think that was poor encouragement.

00:03:22.592 --> 00:03:26.048
Because the reality is that there are giants in the land.

00:03:26.048 --> 00:03:29.184
We do face obstacles in our spiritual journey.

00:03:29.184 --> 00:03:34.688
Because where God calls us to go forward, we have an enemy that doesn't want us to go there.

00:03:35.008 --> 00:03:45.056
And so the key to remembering to be bold is not absence of obstacles, but to say greater is he that is within me than he that is within the world.

00:03:44.576 --> 00:03:48.992
world. And so your spiritual journey, you might be facing obstacles.

00:03:48.832 --> 00:03:51.456
Whether it's fear or anger,

00:03:51.136 --> 00:03:54.240
Or some other abiding sin or just opposition?

00:03:54.304 --> 00:03:57.600
And that's an invitation from Jesus to remember that he is with you.

00:03:57.568 --> 00:04:00.288
And that if you have faith the size of a mustard seed,

00:03:59.968 --> 00:04:02.016
Nothing will be impossible for you.
